Able	Soldier of Thom Tissy's 12th Squad, medium infantry, in the 9th Company of the 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. Part of Adjunct Tavore Paran's punitive expedition against the Army of the Apocalypse. A veteran whose name was already well known among fellow soldiers in the legion before the campaign in Raraku.
Alardis	Commander attached to Admiral Nok's flagship staff as part of the forces assembled by Adjunct Tavore Paran.
Andarist|Darist	Tiste Andii and younger brother of Anomander Rake. Also called Darist, he lived on Drift Avalii with young descendants of his brother and served as one of the guardians of the Throne of Shadow. Extremely tall, ancient, black-skinned, white-haired, and amber-eyed, he carried himself at first like an absent-minded scholar rather than an obvious warrior. Long-lived but not a Soletaken dragon, he had aged, spoke good Malazan haltingly, and held a stoic attitude toward events beyond the island.
Aramala	Jaghut woman of the Jhag Odhan, tall and imposing, with pearlescent grey eyes and a long history of surviving the T'lan Imass. Hidden beneath a stone prison within a tower of Omtose Phellack, Aramala endured as one of the ancient presences still lingering in the odhan.
Astabb	Nathii associate of the slavemaster Silgar in Silver Lake. One of the retainers attached to Silgar's operations in the town, Astabb is lightly sketched and appears among the small group accompanying Borrug during the search for Karsa Orlong.
Bairoth Gild|Bairoth	Young warrior of the Uryd clan of the Teblor, age-contemporary of Karsa Orlong and Delum Thord. Heavier and shorter than his two companions, with a bear-like quality to his build. Rivalled Karsa for the affections of Dayliss and possessed a sharp wit, often deploying words with many-edged meanings that were lost on his rival. One of the three warriors who accompanied Karsa Orlong on the raid to Silver Lake.
Balantis	Fat, elderly Nathii merchant of Silver Lake with a wife, two children, servants, and a prosperous household.
Balgrid	Squad mage in Borduke's 6th Squad, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. Originally overweight, he grew into a thick-chested man described as solid as a tree trunk, with a bearded and appallingly unattractive face. An illusionist specialising in the Meanas warren, with additional facility in necromancy through Hood's Path and in healing through Denul.
Balm	Sergeant commanding the 9th Squad of medium infantry in the 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. A tall, young, wide-shouldered Dal Honese with midnight skin, heavy eyebrows, jutting steering-oar ears, bulging yellowy eyes, and a face described as resembling a squashed gourd. Unusually, Balm was his real name rather than a soldier's nickname. Fiddler noted his cool indifference under pressure as an admirable quality. In the moments before battle, however, he was prone to a temporary disoriented state known as "the Confusion," in which he lost track of everything until fighting actually began. Held a low opinion of nobleborn officers and spoke badly accented Ehrlii.
Borduke	Sergeant commanding the 6th Squad in the 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. Had a habit of pulling and tugging at his beard while deep in thought or under stress. Distrusted Captain Keneb, citing rumours that the captain had survived the Whirlwind by abandoning his men. Rumoured — though never proven — to have once thrown a nobleborn officer off a cliff near Karashimesh.
Borrug	Nathii in the employ of the slavemaster Silgar at Silver Lake, one of the hard-used retainers attached to Silgar's operations in the town.
Bottle	Squad mage and marine in Sergeant Strings' 4th Squad, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. A plain young man, thin as a spear and around twenty years of age; Fiddler noted the diffident bluster typical of young mages in him. His magical abilities derived primarily from witchery and spirit-lore taught to him by his grandmother, supplemented by access to the Warrens of Meanas, Thyr, and Hood's Path. His most distinctive talent was his ability to project his senses through the eyes and ears of animals and insects, making him an exceptional scout. Before enlisting — at the posthumous insistence of his grandmother's spirit — he had been selling charmed dolls to sailors in Jakatakan.
Bowl	Huge, mean-looking heavy infantryman in the 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army, likely belonging to Sobelone's squad. Despite the general reputation of heavies for brawn over brains, Bowl showed an impressive aptitude for picking up new military specialties quickly.
Braven Tooth|Master Sergeant Braven Tooth	Grizzled master sergeant of the Malazan army based at the Malaz City garrison, infamous for training recruits through intimidation and for bestowing the nicknames many soldiers came to wear as their real names. A huge, filthy, black-haired veteran with a reputation stretching back decades, Braven Tooth loomed large in Malazan military lore.
Burnt	Corporal in Sergeant Moak's 11th Squad, medium infantry, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. Part of Adjunct Tavore Paran's punitive expedition against the Army of the Apocalypse. His name was well known among soldiers of the legion alongside those of Moak and Stacker.
Calm	Female Forkrul Assail known among Teblor legend as a "Forkassal" and remembered as a Bringer of Peace. Imprisoned beneath a massive stone on the Laederon Plateau for ages untold, she was a figure of dread and worship to those who knew the old stories surrounding her prison.
Corabb Bhilan Thenu'alas	Pardu officer in Leoman's company during the Whirlwind rebellion, famed for unwavering devotion and fierce battlefield zeal. Sixth son of a deposed chief and long a wanderer, Corabb fought with long-hafted axe-like weapons and carried scarab shells against evil, combining fanatic loyalty with a blunt, earnest presence.
Cord|Sergeant Cord	Sergeant of the 5th Squad of the Ashok Regiment under Captain Kindly. A dark-skinned Seven Cities native with a scarred face, a tattoo-stitched bald pate, and a gleaming row of gold teeth, Cord was a seasoned infantryman and a dependable field leader among the Ashok veterans.
Cynnigig	Ancient Jaghut of the Jhag Odhan, bent, gaunt, talkative, and proudly ignorant of the wider world's concerns. A survivor of old betrayals and a lover of horses, Cynnigig combined great age, evasive cunning, and comic verbosity in a way that made him one of the odhan's strangest lingering powers.
Damisk	Nathii hunter and tracker who had previously served in the Greydog army during the Malazan conquest before becoming an associate of the slavemaster Silgar in Silver Lake. His brow was marked with a tribal tattoo.
Dayliss	Young woman of the Uryd clan of the Teblor, the object of rivalry between Karsa Orlong and Bairoth Gild for her affections.
Deadsmell	Corporal and squad mage in Sergeant Balm's 9th Squad of medium infantry in the 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. A broad-chested man with a bearded chin and mostly hairless brows, his name was bestowed by Master Sergeant Braven Tooth. The squad's healer, he had access to High Denul. His necromantic abilities were rooted in skills acquired during his youth in the village of Gethran before his military service, drawing on Hood's Warren.
Delum Thord|Delum	Young warrior of the Uryd clan of the Teblor, age-contemporary of Karsa Orlong and Bairoth Gild. Quiet by nature and given to keeping his own counsel, contrasting with his more vocal companions. One of the three warriors who set out with Karsa on the raid to Silver Lake.
Duryl	Messenger in Sha'ik's Army of the Apocalypse, a minor functionary serving the rebellion's command structure in Raraku. Lightly sketched, he belongs to the network of couriers and subordinates who kept the army's internal communications moving in the days surrounding the Battle of Raraku.
Ebron	Squad mage of Cord's 5th Squad in the Ashok Regiment. Born in Karakarang, Ebron wielded the warrens of Ruse and Rashan and was valued for dangerous, forceful battlefield sorcery, a dry wit, and the wary professionalism of a veteran mage who understood exactly how lethal his work could be.
Enias	Young Tiste Liosan warrior serving under Seneschal Jorrude, proud, pale, and eager to prove himself with the sword. Like his companions, Enias embodied the stern arrogance and martial certainty of the Liosan hunting their enemies through shattered warrens and into Seven Cities.
Ethume	Corporal serving in Sha'ik's Army of the Apocalypse among the rebel forces gathered in Raraku. A subordinate soldier in the army's structure, briefly glimpsed in the tense days leading up to the Battle of Raraku.
Fayelle	Sorceress in Sha'ik's Army of the Apocalypse and one of Kamist Reloe's lieutenants alongside Henaras. Described as obese and perpetually nervous yet genuinely dangerous, she was implied to possess a Soletaken or D'ivers nature. A former instructor of Sinn, Fayelle carries a dark history that precedes the rebellion and makes her one of the Whirlwind's more ominous magical figures.
Flashwit	Heavy infantrywoman in Sergeant Mosel's squad, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. A burly, round-faced Napan, she had shaved her head, wore a bronze nose-ring, and possessed arm muscles of intimidating size; the ground seemed to tremble when she walked. Her most striking feature was a pair of startlingly beautiful emerald green eyes, unusual enough to suggest her heritage extended beyond Napan. One of three soldiers known as the "dread ladies" of the heavy infantry alongside Mayfly and Uru Hela.
Galt	Pardu tribesman and medium infantryman in Sergeant Balm's 9th Squad, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. Marked by facial tattoos and counted among the soldiers whose fighting reputation was already well established in the legion.
Ganal	Warrior of the Sunyd clan of the Teblor of northern Genabackis, held as a prisoner by the slavemaster Silgar. Quick to insult the rival Uryd clan, Ganal is one of the Teblor captives held in Silgar's custody.
Gentur	Kanese marine in Malazan service, heavily armoured with a visored helm and armed with a crossbow. He is among the Malazan marines present on Drift Avalii following an encounter between their fleet and Tiste Edur ships.
Gnaw	Hunting dog and pack-leader of a Rathyd clan pack.
Greyfrog	Dog-sized demon companion of L'oric, reptilian in form, endlessly hungry, and possessed of a telepathic voice by turns grandiose, comic, and earnest. Born of darkness and violence, Greyfrog is more than a mere familiar — capable of a strange loyalty and an unexpected tenderness beneath its fearsome nature.
Grub	Orphan boy adopted by Captain Keneb from among the survivors of the Chain of Dogs, raised in the company of the Malaz 14th Army. A toddler with a tangled shock of blond hair and a deeply tanned, cherubic face often smeared with dirt. Despite no formal mage training, unaccountably attuned to the mystical aspects of the world.
Gullstream	Crossbowman of the Ehrlitan Guard serving as medium infantry in Thom Tissy's 12th Squad of the Malaz 14th Army. Dark-skinned and striking, with a high blotched forehead and the habit of wiping his runny nose on his sleeve.
Haran Epal	Logros T'lan Imass clansman in Ibra Gholan's company, one of the undead hunters pursuing the Unbound through the Nascent and into the struggle surrounding the First Throne. Though lightly sketched, Haran Epal stands among the stern ancient retainers of Logros duty.
Havok (Jhag horse)	Iron-grey Jhag stallion chosen and named by Karsa Orlong. Just entering adulthood when selected, the horse had a sleek, rippling iron-grey hide with a white or silver mane and tail — distinctive among Jhag horses, whose wiry manes are typically black. Long-legged, gaunt, and fierce, Havok possessed remarkable speed and endurance: capable of maintaining a canter for half a day, dropping to a lope for a bell's span, and resuming a canter until dusk, at a full gallop easily outpacing a conventional Seven Cities steed.
Havok (Teblor warhorse)	Prized destrier belonging to Synyg Orlong of the Uryd clan. Standing at twenty-six hands high — nearly twice the height and mass of lowlander breeds — Havok was a formidable war mount, representative of the massive horses bred by the Teblor, themselves noted as smaller cousins of the Jhag horses of the Jhag Odhan.
Hawl	Old witch whose warren was Ruse, former commander of the Talon and one of the first of Kellanved's family. She disappeared following Kellanved's vanishing and has long been unaccounted for. Wife of Admiral Nok.
Henaras	Sorceress in the Army of the Apocalypse, alongside Fayelle as one of Kamist Reloe's lieutenants. Banished from her desert tribe and preserving a youthful appearance through magic, Henaras cultivated an air of languid menace and was trusted with potent wards and close protection.
Hubb	Corporal in Borduke's 6th Squad, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. Part of Adjunct Tavore Paran's punitive expedition against the Army of the Apocalypse. Present at the 9th Company scorpion fight on the road to Raraku.
Ibb	Marine in Borduke's 6th Squad, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. Part of Adjunct Tavore Paran's punitive expedition against the Army of the Apocalypse. Served as the vocal colour commentator during the inter-squad scorpion fights organised on the road to Raraku.
Ibra Gholan	Logros T'lan Imass clan leader, clad in the skin of a dhenrabi and carrying the grave authority of his people. He leads a party of Logros hunters in pursuit of the Unbound — seven renegade clansmen — and embodies the stern command structure of the Logros clans.
Imrahl	Ancient Khundryl warrior serving as aide to Gall of the Khundryl Burned Tears.
Irriz|Captain Irriz	Renegade former corporal of the 3rd Company of the Ashok Regiment who joined the Whirlwind rebellion and promoted himself to captain. Wearing the trappings of a Malazan officer while leading a rebel force in Seven Cities, Irriz was especially driven by hatred for Captain Kindly and the Ashok veterans who had remained loyal.
Jibb	Former member of the Ehrlitan Guard who serves as a medium infantryman in Thom Tissy's 12th Squad of the Malaz 14th Army.
Jorrude	Tiste Liosan seneschal and warrior-priest of Osric, a tall, pale, silver-haired commander whose sour severity and rigid sense of order made him emblematic of his people. He led a small band of Liosan through the shattered warrens in pursuit of trespassers and enemies, carrying the pride and grievance of Kurald Thyrllan with him.
Karsa Orlong|Karsa	Young warrior of the Uryd clan of the Teblor people, inhabiting the Laederon Plateau on the northern edge of Genabackis. Already into his eightieth year when he set out from his village, yet still considered a youngster by Teblor standards given their extended lifespan. A giant of a man, over seven feet tall and powerfully muscled. Driven by the desire to outdo the legendary raid of his grandfather Pahlk on Silver Lake, he set out with companions Bairoth Gild and Delum Thord to raid foreign territories and bring glory to the Uryd clan.
Kasanal	Assassin in the employ of Korbolo Dom and formerly a Semk shaman, noted for his relish in killing and his preference for Malazan victims over Seven Cities natives. Likely among the group of Dom's appallingly skilled killers drawn from the Dogslayers, Kasanal combined a ritual background with a direct taste for violence.
Keeper|Ba'ienrok	Reclusive giant of Napan appearance living alone in a fossil-filled tower on the shore of the Otataral Sea. Calling himself Keeper and translating his local name Ba'ienrock for visitors, he was a formidable, secretive man with a paleontologist's obsession and a past he preferred buried.
Kindly|Captain Kindly	Captain in Malazan service commanding the 2nd Company of the Ashok Regiment. Renowned as one of the harshest and most intimidating officers in the Malazan military, Kindly was feared for his discipline, legendary caution, and savage tongue, yet also showed a hard-edged concern for the soldiers under his command. He was notably bald, obsessively proud of his collection of combs, and locked in a famously adversarial partnership with his lieutenant, Pores.
Koryk	Marine in Sergeant Strings' 4th Squad, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. A large, half-Seti youth with a flat-featured face, broad shoulders, and long black hair that had a tendency to whip across his face. Conflicted over his mixed heritage, he decorated himself with Seti fetishes in homage to his roots yet chose to enlist in the marines rather than the cavalry as his Seti blood might otherwise have directed. Fiddler saw in him the mailed fist that every squad needed. Frequently came into conflict with his squadmate Smiles.
L'oric	High Mage of the Apocalypse army, affiliated with the Army of the Whirlwind and able to call upon Denul when required. Tall, thin-faced, pale-haired, haughty, and usually robed in white, he was not naturally approachable or given to drama. Among Sha'ik's high mages he was regarded as formidable, mysterious, reliable, and pragmatic rather than faithful, with a weave of sorcery about him that kept his thoughts hidden.
Limp	Malazan soldier of Cord's 5th Squad in the 2nd Company of the Ashok Regiment. His nickname came from a training accident involving Braven Tooth and a fallen horse, and repeated leg injuries made the name stick with darkly comic inevitability.
Lobe	Medium infantryman in Sergeant Balm's 9th Squad of the 9th Company, 8th Legion, Malaz 14th Army. Not especially thoughtful by his own inclination but reliable with his weapons, Lobe was a steady presence in the squad.
Lutes	Squad healer in Borduke's 6th Squad, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. A quiet, small man. Part of Adjunct Tavore Paran's punitive expedition against the Army of the Apocalypse.
Malachar	Tiste Liosan warrior in Jorrude's company, stern, pale, and armored in the ornate style of his people. Malachar carried the same harsh certainty and zeal for righteous violence that marked the Liosan band hunting enemies through the Nascent and beyond.
Mathok	Tall, fierce warleader of the desert tribes in the Army of the Apocalypse and a close ally of Leoman, widely regarded as beloved among the desert peoples despite a grating personality. A black-skinned, taciturn warrior with a weathered face and an air of innate nobility, Mathok embodied the martial authority of the tribal host gathered under Sha'ik.
Maybe	Marine sapper in Borduke's 6th Squad, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. Originally from Aren, he had pale green eyes and was physically sickened in the presence of sorcery. Known within the company for his exceptional ability to retain facts. Before uniform standardisation, he wore a brass loop on one ear from which hung a human finger bone. Had a dry, satirical streak.
Moak	Sergeant of the 11th Squad, medium infantry, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. A copper-haired and bearded Falari, bearing a lance scar that ran the full length of his back from shoulders to tailbone. Renowned among his fellow soldiers for seeming to 'know things' — his hunches were passed along only to Tugg and Sobelone. His speculations included that Borduke had once thrown a nobleborn officer off a cliff near Karashimesh, and that Gesler had served as an under-age marine under Dassem Ultor, Cartheron Crust, or Urko Crust. Possessed an iron stomach — a rotten-fish stew he prepared on the road to Raraku left his entire squad ill while he himself suffered only belches.
Monok Ochem	T'lan Imass Bonecaster of the Logros nation, massively boned with disproportionately long arms. The black fur he wore around his shoulders faded to silver where it formed a mangled hood around his head. He led a party of Logros in pursuit of the Unbound — seven renegade clansmen — tracking them into the Nascent. Harsh in judgment and uncompromising toward any who deviated from Logros duty, Monok Ochem exercised the full authority of a Bonecaster and wielded the warren of Tellann.
Mosel	Sergeant of heavy infantry in the 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. A lean man with epicanthic folds suggesting Kanese blood, wearing his hair braided and cut finger-length in the fashion of Jakatakan pirates — a typical mixed-heritage product of Malaz City. Protective of the soldiers under his command and quick to bristle at any perceived mockery directed at them. The youngest of the three heavy sergeants — alongside Sobelone and Tugg — who shared a threatening air that had less to do with size than attitude, and who resembled each other closely enough to pass for siblings.
Mudslinger	Malazan marine serving as medium infantry in Thom Tissy's 12th Squad of the Malaz 14th Army. A tough soldier with a reputation for surviving the edges of disaster.
Olar Shayn	Logros T'lan Imass clansman in Ibra Gholan's company, distinguished by his rotted wolf fur and bone-hafted axe. He stands among the ancient hunters pursuing the Unbound renegades, carrying the bleak endurance typical of his people.
Onrack T'emlava|Onrack|Onrack the Broken	Clanless Logros T'lan Imass, bearing an obsidian blade and an ancient burden of failure and exile. Unlike most of his kin, Onrack is more deeply defined by memory, reflection, and a restless inward fracture than by duty or martial purpose — a quality that sets him apart among the undead warriors of his people.
Orenas	Low-ranking Tiste Liosan warrior in Jorrude's band, pale and silver-haired like his companions but more often left with the practical duties of guard and retainer. Orenas helps give shape to the small, severe Liosan company stalking their foes through broken warrens and foreign lands.
Pahlk Orlong|Pahlk	Elder of the Uryd clan of the Teblor and grandfather of Karsa Orlong, venerated within the village as the last warrior to have led successful raids beyond Teblor lands. His tales of a youthful foray to Silver Lake were celebrated among the clan and served as the inspiration for his grandson's ambitions.
Phyrlis	Ancient Jaghut woman bound within the living body of a colossal tree on a hill in the Jhag Odhan, speaking softly by thought rather than by voice. Joined in strange symbiosis with the tree that preserved her, Phyrlis was an eerie yet nurturing presence tied to the survival of the odhan's Jhag horses.
Pores|Lieutenant Pores	Lieutenant Aramstos Pores, the long-suffering subordinate of Captain Kindly in the Ashok Regiment. Sharp-witted and sardonic, he was one of the few soldiers able to match Kindly word for word, and their famously combative partnership was already one of the army's most talked-about double acts.
Ramp	Medium infantryman of Thom Tissy's 12th Squad in the 9th Company of the 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. A veteran whose name was already well known among fellow soldiers in the legion before the campaign in Raraku.
Ranal	Young, noble-born Lieutenant commanding the 4th, 5th, and 6th Marine squads in the 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army, under Captain Keneb. A tall Quon man, fair-skinned and fair-haired, with high cheekbones, a wide straight nose, a full mouth, pale blue eyes, and a clean-shaven face. In front of his soldiers he adopted a grim officer's expression meant to project maturity, though his inexperience in field conditions was apparent to the veterans under his nominal command.
Sands	Marine, sapper, and minor mage in Gesler's 5th Squad, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. Part of Adjunct Tavore Paran's expedition against the Army of the Apocalypse.
Scillara	Camp follower in Sha'ik's army in the Raraku desert, voluptuous and known for a throaty laugh. Her mother had been a camp follower of the Ashok Regiment and her father one of its soldiers; when the regiment was posted overseas, both were abandoned, and her mother soon died. Eventually taken under the care of High Mage Bidithal, Scillara developed a sharp intelligence beneath an outwardly intoxicated and compliant surface, and smoked rustleaf habitually.
Scrawl	Member of the Ehrlitan Guard, briefly glimpsed among the garrison soldiers stationed in the city. A minor figure whose handiwork drew admiring comments from fellow guards.
Shard|Corporal Shard	Corporal in Cord's squad in the Ashok Regiment. A young but hard and capable soldier, Shard is the half-brother of Sinn and remains fiercely protective of her. His blunt practicality and stubborn endurance mark him as a reliable fighting man.
Shortnose	Heavy infantryman in the 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army, in either Sobelone's or Tugg's squad. Mean-looking, with huge hands and the tip of his nose cut off at some point in the past — the evident source of his name. Prone to extraordinarily loud snoring.
Silgar|Slavemaster Silgar	Nathii slavemaster and priest of Mael based in Silver Lake. A tall, thin man with a severe, weather-lined face, he wore deep blue shimmering clothing trimmed with intricate patterns of gold thread. He made his fortune trafficking Teblor of the Sunyd clan.
Sinn	Young mage of Malazan descent living in Seven Cities, slight and pallid with light brown eyes. Half-sister to Shard, a member of the Ashok Regiment. She studied magic for a time with the sorceress Fayelle, an experience she describes as unpleasant, and carries a deep personal grievance against her former instructor rooted in events that preceded the Whirlwind rebellion. Though she described her own talents as minor magicks, those around her sensed something more unsettling beneath the surface.
Smiles	Marine in Sergeant Strings' 4th Squad, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. Petite in build and disinclined to smile — the source of her pseudonym, assigned by Master Sergeant Braven Tooth. She preferred attacking from stealth and was skilled with the two thin-bladed knives she kept on her belt, serving as one of the squad's night scouts. The remorseless chill of her eyes hinted at a violent past. Frequently came into conflict with her squadmate Koryk.
Sobelone	Sergeant of heavy infantry in the 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. A severe-looking woman with streaks of grey in her shoulder-length black hair and eyes the colour of the sky. The oldest of the three heavy sergeants — alongside Mosel and Tugg — who together projected a threatening air that had less to do with size than attitude and who resembled each other closely enough to pass for siblings. Shared intelligence with Tugg through Sergeant Moak, who was reputed to 'know things'.
Squint	Veteran bowman of the Aren Guard and renowned marksman in Aren. Short and squat, with forearms muscled like hemp ropes, eyes like small black marbles nested in wrinkles, a bald head but for a fringe of long grey ratty strands, and a longbow as tall as himself. His uniform appeared not to have been washed or repaired in decades. A soldier of deep experience and fearsome reputation with the bow, he serves in Blistig's 9th Legion within Adjunct Tavore Paran's 14th Army.
Stacker	Corporal in Sergeant Moak's 11th Squad, medium infantry, in the 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. One of the soldiers whose name was already well known in the legion during Tavore's campaign across Seven Cities, Stacker was part of the tough core of veterans serving under Moak.
Synyg Orlong|Synyg	Son of Pahlk Orlong and father of Karsa Orlong, a warrior of the Uryd clan of the Teblor. Considered a disappointment to Pahlk for his reluctance to venture beyond the village and raid foreign territories. Owner of the prized destrier Havok.
T'morol	Grizzled, burly bodyguard to Mathok in the Army of the Whirlwind. His cold dark eyes were impervious to surprise, his face hard and weathered with a beard, and he wore leather armour with a scimitar and round shield at his hip. Said to look like some upright, hairless wolf, he was a hunter through and through — fiercely loyal and always at his warchief's side.
Tarr	Corporal in Sergeant Strings' 4th Squad, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. A nondescript Hengan with pale, stolid features, placid pallid eyes, and a greying beard. Rather than carrying his oversized shield on his back like most soldiers, he kept it strapped to his left hand at all times, his equipment pack fitted with quick-release clasps so he could shed it with one hand while the other reached for his short thick-bladed sword. His scaled iron hauberk provided what he found a satisfying anchoring weight. He rarely spoke and was slow to act without orders — qualities Strings considered ideal in a corporal. His name derived from his time as a recruit, when Master Sergeant Braven Tooth spent nearly two bells attempting to dislodge him with a mace and could not move him once he had planted his feet behind his shield.
Tavos Pond	Meanas mage and marine in Gesler's 5th Squad, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. A tall, dark, moustached man of probable Korelri origin, part of Adjunct Tavore Paran's punitive expedition against the Army of the Apocalypse.
Temul	Wickan warrior of the Foolish Dog clan. A scrawny, peach-faced lancer first encountered among the Wickan horse warriors accompanying High Fist Coltaine's 7th Army, he participated in the Chain of Dogs — the grueling overland march across Seven Cities to the Malazan bastion at Aren. He serves in the Malaz 14th Army during its campaign in Seven Cities.
Thom Tissy	Sergeant of the 12th Squad, medium infantry, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. Virtually hairless, with a face that might be handsome to a female toad — cheeks heavily pocked, the backs of his hands covered in warts, dark beady eyes, calloused hands, and short bandy legs that left him as squat as an ogre. Wore a singular expression of disapproval as his default countenance. Despite his grim appearance, he was supportive and encouraging toward both his troops and superior officers.
Throatslitter	Hengese marine in Sergeant Balm's 9th Squad of medium infantry in the 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. Pale-eyed, with scars on his neck and a habitually murderous expression. Carried twin long-knives in gloved hands. Possessed an uncanny shrieking laugh capable of silencing an entire tavern. Held a dim view of priests.
Torvald Nom|Knuckles|Torvald	Daru ne'er-do-well of House Nom, known to his Malazan enemies as "Knuckles." Cousin of Rallick Nom and estranged from his family, Torvald organised the bandits of Fool's Forest and Yellow Mark Forest in resistance to Malazan rule before his luck ran out. Tall, wiry, and scarred, with a self-described sporadic education and little talent for acquiring friends, he possessed a resourceful tongue and an instinct for turning bad situations to his advantage.
Traveller	Mysterious swordsman of extraordinary skill whose very presence unsettles gods and old soldiers alike. Marked by immense power, deep restraint, and the weight of old anger, he moves through the world like a legend in plain sight — a figure whose past and true nature remain deliberately obscured.
Trull Sengar	Tiste Edur of House Sengar, second son of Tomad and Uruth, renowned for integrity, intellect, and a nearly compulsive truthfulness. Bald, scarred, and deadly with a spear, Trull stands apart from his kin for his modesty, self-awareness, and moral unease — qualities that make him one of the most reflective and quietly honourable figures among the Edur.
Tugg	Sergeant of heavy infantry in the 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army, hailing from Malaz City. The largest of the three heavy sergeants — alongside Mosel and Sobelone — with a thin, grating voice attributed to a damaged larynx. Carried a short single-bladed axe paired with an enormous hardwood shield sheathed in tin and rimmed in bronze, worn strapped to his back. He and his fellow heavy sergeants shared a threatening air that had less to do with size than attitude, and resembled each other closely enough to pass for siblings.
Uru Hela	Heavy infantrywoman in Sergeant Mosel's squad, 9th Company, 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. Originally from Korel, she was surmised by Gesler to have been destined for service on the Stormwall before stowing away aboard a Jakatakan merchantman — a past he read as meaning she felt she owed nobody anything. One of three soldiers known as the "dread ladies" of the heavy infantry alongside Flashwit and Mayfly. Notable for a firm dislike of dishonesty.
Widdershins	Squad mage in Sergeant Balm's 9th Squad of medium infantry in the 8th Legion of the Malaz 14th Army. Described as an odd little man. Drew on the Warren of Meanas, the warren of illusions and deception.
